1. What are the types of comments in Java?
-->🔹 1. Types of Comments in Java

      Java supports 3 types of comments:
      
      Single-line comment
      
      // This is a single-line comment
      
      Multi-line comment
      
      /* This is a
         multi-line comment */
      
      Documentation comment (Javadoc)
      
      /**
       * This is a documentation comment
       */


2. Difference between single-line and multi-line comments.
-->
| Feature       | Single-line (`//`)             | Multi-line (`/* */`) |
| ------------- | ------------------------------ | -------------------- |
| Lines covered | Only one line                  | Multiple lines       |
| Syntax        | `// comment`                   | `/* comment */`      |
| Usage         | Short notes                    | Large explanations   |
| Ending        | Ends automatically at line end | Must close with `*/` |



3. Can comments be nested?
-->❌ No, Java does NOT support nested comments

    👉 Example (invalid):
    
    /* Outer comment
       /* Inner comment */
    */
    
    👉 This will cause a compilation error


4. Are comments compiled into bytecode?
-->❌ No
    
    👉 Comments are:
    
    Ignored by the compiler
    Not included in .class (bytecode) files
    
    ✔ They exist only in source code


5. What is the purpose of comments in coding standards or documentation?
-->Explain code logic
  Improve readability
  Help other developers understand code
  Provide documentation (using Javadoc)
  Make maintenance easier
  Describe methods, parameters, and usage
